question: I have several autoimmune disorders and my endocrinologist says I'm at risk for type I diabetes. He has me testing my blood weekly(which is usually just above 100) and using ketostix monthly. This week the ketostix are measuring "trace.". Do I need to be concerned?  Finger sticks registered under 100 this week, and, I feel fine. Thanks for any help.
title: Questionable ketostix result
